                <h1>Understanding Hedgehogs: Fun Facts and Care Tips</h1>
                <p>Hedgehogs are small, nocturnal mammals known for their distinct spiny coats made of stiff, hollow hairs. Native to Europe, Asia, and Africa, these creatures possess the unique ability to roll into a ball when threatened, showcasing their protective spines. Hedgehogs are insectivores, feasting primarily on insects, snails, and worms.</p>
